<tt>epkginfo</tt> is a tool used to display package metadata information. It is a shortcut to using the <tt>equery meta</tt> command.

__TOC__

== Installation ==

=== Emerge ===

<tt>epkginfo</tt> comes as part of the Gentoolkit suite. It, along with the rest of the tools, can be installed by running:

{{Emerge|app-portage/gentoolkit}}

Please see the main [[Gentoolkit|Gentoolkit article]] for information on the other tools included in the {{Package|app-portage/gentoolkit}} package.

== Usage ==

{{Cmd|epkginfo|output=<pre>
Usage: epkginfo [options] pkgspec

Display metadata about a given package.

options
 -h, --help              display this help message
 -d, --description       show an extended package description
 -H, --herd              show the herd(s) for the package
 -k, --keywords          show keywords for all matching package versions
 -l, --license           show licenses for the best maching version
 -m, --maintainer        show the maintainer(s) for the package
 -S, --stablreq          show STABLEREQ arches (cc's) for all matching package versions
 -u, --useflags          show per-package USE flag descriptions
 -U, --upstream          show package's upstream information
 -x, --xml               show the plain metadata.xml file
</pre>}}

=== Invocation ===

As mentioned above <tt>epkginfo</tt> can be invoked two different ways:

{{Cmd|epkginfo}}

Or

{{Cmd|equery meta}}

